# UX Spec
**Project:** {{ project_name }}

## Non-negotiable rules
- Never lose user input on error. Always preserve form state when an operation fails.
- Every async action must show a loading state. The UI must not appear frozen.
- Destructive actions always require a confirmation dialog before executing.
- No placeholder copy (`…`, `TODO`, `[to be defined]`) in any committed UI.

## Loading states
| Pattern | When to use | Implementation |
|---------|-------------|----------------|
| Skeleton | Initial page or section load | Pulse animation on placeholder blocks matching content shape |
| Spinner | Button action (submit, save, delete) | Replace button label with spinner, disable button |
| Progress bar | File upload or long multi-step operation | Show percent complete. Update every second minimum. |

## Feedback & notifications
| Event | Mechanism | Duration | Dismissable | Position |
|-------|-----------|----------|-------------|----------|
| Success | Toast — green | 4s auto-dismiss | yes | Bottom right |
| Validation error | Inline, below the field | Until corrected | no | Adjacent to field |
| Server error | Toast — red | Persistent | yes | Bottom right |
| Confirmation required | Modal dialog | Until user acts | no | Center |

## Confirmation dialogs
<!-- AI: Use this exact dialog structure for all destructive actions. -->
Required before: deleting records, bulk actions, any irreversible operation.
```
Title: "[Verb] [item name]?"  — e.g. "Delete invoice 0042?"
Body: "This cannot be undone."
Actions:
  [Cancel] (left, neutral)
  [Confirm action] (right, danger-styled)
```

## Forms
- Validate on blur (not on every keystroke, not only on submit).
- After first failed submit: show all validation errors at once.
- Autofocus the first field when a modal opens.
- Disable the submit button while a request is in flight.
- On create success: reset the form.
- On edit success: retain the updated values.
- Tab order must follow visual layout order.

## Navigation
- Active route is always visually highlighted in the nav.
- Browser back button works for all navigations (no history.replace on success).
- Deep links must work without requiring click-through navigation.
- After login, redirect to the originally requested URL (not always dashboard).

## Empty states
<!-- AI: Every list, table, feed, and search result must have a defined empty state. -->
Required structure: Heading + 1-line description + CTA (if the user can take action).
```
Example:
  Heading: "No invoices yet"
  Body: "Create your first invoice to get started."
  CTA: [Create invoice →] (links to create flow)
```

## Breakpoints
| Name | Width | Notes |
|------|-------|-------|
| Mobile | < 768px | Stack all columns. Touch-friendly tap targets (≥ 44px). |
| Tablet | 768–1024px | Reduce column count. Collapsible nav. |
| Desktop | > 1024px | Full layout as designed. |
